President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Mississippi and authorized Federal assistance to support recovery efforts from severe storms, flooding, and mudslides that occurred from February 10 to February 18, 2020. The declaration allows for Federal funding to be provided on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities in various affected counties. Additionally, funding is available for statewide hazard mitigation measures. Terry L. Quarles has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made if requested by the State and based on damage assessments. For more information, media should contact the FEMA News Desk.